article.headline: Austin Peay 69, Tennessee State 51
article.story: CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Anthony Davis scored 22 points to lead Austin Peay to a 69-51 victory over cold-shooting Tennessee State on Thursday night. The Governors (7-13, 5-3 Ohio Valley Conference) blew open a close game in the second half by shooting 56 percent, while the Tigers (9-12, 4-3) shot just 24.4 percent in the final 20 minutes and 29.5 percent for the game. Maurice Hampton scored 13 points and Zac Schlader added 11 for Austin Peay, and William Durden grabbed 10 rebounds. Eric King scored 15 points for Tennessee State and Rod Flowers had eight rebounds. Austin Peay took a 25-17 lead with 3:20 left in the first half on a layup by Schlader, and led 27-21 at the break. The Governors ran away with the game in the second half, taking their first double-digit lead at 31-21 with 18:01 left on a jump shot by Hampton. From there, Austin Peay went on a 29-13 run capped by a 3-pointer from Levi Carmichael to lead 59-34 with 7:21 to play. The Governors shot 48.1 percent from the field for the game.
